{
  "stem": "3040.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not an official yeshiva the way you know it here.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was every shtiebel, every beit midrash had somebody who was lecturing on Talmud and on Tanakh.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is where I was getting my education, my Jewish education, my Hebrew education.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say, well, if you-- if you figure that I started cheder when-- at the age of three, then it was-- I had probably 18 years of schooling.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it all depends how much one can retain when he is three years old.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Shabbas was a special day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because all the problems, you, you tried to forget about everything that was going on that troubled you.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All problems were put aside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Friday afternoon, we used to go to the mikvah, which it's maybe not in the same sense as you know a mikvah here.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was actually a Turkish bath.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I used to love to go there in the Friday afternoon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you spend it for two hours.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and it's baths, Turkish baths.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And after this, we used to go to a place where you used to have a cold beer and something, some salami.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is how the Shabbat actually started.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then in the evening, we would go to services, not unlike people here go to services Friday evening, except that the services were conducted in a completely different manner that you would know here.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You would find it here also, in Borough Park.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's approximately the same type of services.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then after the services, in the evening, there was a very elaborate Shabbat dinner.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And noodles and chicken soup was on the table every Shabbat dinner, and chicken.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And while at the table, we're singing all kinds of songs, which in Hebrew Z'mirot.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
